LOCAL
=====

Search all code for GETSTARTED comments

Change website name in pages/tos.html and pages/privacy.html

Copy database.yml from other project and change database name:

  cp ../claimtask/config/database.yml config && \
    e config/database.yml

  be rake db:setup



HEROKU
======

Create heroku app:

  heroku create APPNAME
  git remote add production https://git.heroku.com/APPNAME.git

Add heroku add-ons:

  heroku addons:create heroku-postgresql:hobby-dev
  heroku addons:create heroku-redis:hobby-dev
  heroku addons:create logentries
  heroku addons:create rollbar
  heroku addons:create postmark
  heroku addons:create newrelic

Schedule postgres backups:

  heroku pg:backups schedule DATABASE_URL --at '02:00 Europe/Berlin'

Back up backups to VPS:

  ssh vps "echo APPNAME >> ~/heroku_backups/apps; cat ~/heroku_backups/apps"

Deploy to Heroku:

  git push production master
  heroku run rake db:migrate



HEROKU QUICKSTART
=================

Set the app name and copy paste this:

APPNAME=xxxx
heroku create $APPNAME                                                        && \
  git remote add production https://git.heroku.com/$APPNAME.git               && \
  heroku addons:create heroku-postgresql:hobby-dev                            && \
  heroku addons:create heroku-redis:hobby-dev                                 && \
  heroku addons:create logentries                                             && \
  heroku addons:create rollbar                                                && \
  heroku addons:create postmark                                               && \
  heroku addons:create newrelic                                               && \
  heroku pg:backups schedule DATABASE_URL --at '02:00 Europe/Berlin'          && \
  ssh vps "echo $APPNAME >> ~/heroku_backups/apps; cat ~/heroku_backups/apps" && \
  git push production master                                                  && \
  heroku run rake db:migrate
